ild artifacts**.\" |\n\n### Consequences\n\nPer the consequences map:\n\n| If you change... | Also update... | Applicable? |\n|---|---|---|\n| A script in `.agent/scripts/` | Script reference table in `AGENTS.md` | No — no new scripts, just fixing existing ones |\n| Worktree scripts | `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md`; `AGENTS.md` worktree section | Check — if either doc mentions build sourcing behavior, update to match |\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- The suggested fix (export `ROS2_LAYERS_BASE` from `worktree_enter.sh`, respect it in `setup.bash`) is clean. One refinement: ensure the detection logic on lines 31-41 of `setup.bash` is still evaluated as a fallback (for cases where `setup.bash` is sourced directly from a worktree directory without going through `worktree_enter.sh`).\n- Add a brief verification step to the PR: from a layer worktree, run `echo $ROS2_LAYERS_BASE` and confirm it points to the worktree, not `layers/main/`.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772649400,"nonce":"FBZ/IJpqO8xkmFOGvYxHM32Xjqw=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87vz3DCzwAAAAVq_d5D"},"status":2}]}